message.content: One of the most significant events that occurred in Iraq in the past five years was the defeat of the Islamic State of Iraq and Syria (ISIS) in 2017. After years of conflict and territorial gains by ISIS, a coalition of Iraqi security forces, Kurdish Peshmerga fighters, and international allies launched a major offensive to retake the territories occupied by the extremist group. The operation, known as the Battle of Mosul, resulted in the liberation of Iraq's second-largest city, Mosul, which had been under ISIS control since 2014. This victory marked a turning point in the fight against ISIS and significantly weakened the group's presence in Iraq.
